{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LDsNccgcprk9pgaRM4G7mn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n     2→\n     3→---\n     4→\n     5→### 3-3-onboard-alias — create-story (2026-03-21T04:24Z)\n     6→\n     7→- **Previous sprint file collision:** An existing `3-3-bmad-parser-story-bridge-command.md` exists from a previous sprint's Epic 3. No conflict since new file uses `3-3-onboard-alias.md`.\n     8→- **Ambiguous AC3:** Epic says `codeharness onboard scan` should map to \"equivalent audit subcommand,\" but audit has no subcommands. Interpreted as deprecation warning + base audit run.\n     9→- **Risk: Old exports removal.** `onboard.ts` exports `getLastScanResult()`, `getLastCoverageResult()`, `getLastAuditResult()`, and `resetLastScanResult()`. Need to verify no external consumers before removing.\n    10→- **Risk: `onboard epic` subcommand has no audit equivalent.** Dropping silently may surprise users.\n    11→\n    12→### 3-3-onboard-alias — dev-story (2026-03-21T04:31Z)\n    13→\n    14→- **audit-action.ts branch coverage 95.83%:** Two uncovered branches (lines 96, 101) in JSON fix output formatting. Covered by audit.test.ts but not onboard.test.ts — redundant since both delegate to same handler.\n    15→- **Test file size:** onboard.test.ts is 325 lines vs estimated 100-150. Consistent with project norms (audit.test.ts is 407 lines).\n    16→- **console.log in shared handler:** audit-action.ts line 107 uses console.log directly. Story says \"Do NOT use console.log directly\" but formatAuditHuman() returns pre-formatted strings — wrapping in ok()/info() would double-prefix.\n    17→\n    18→### 3-3-onboard-alias — code-review (2026-03-21T04:38Z)\n    19→\n    20→- **HIGH: Unsafe double type assertion** in audit-action.ts:86 — `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` bypassed type safety. Fixed with spread operator.\n    21→- **MEDIUM: Dead branch guard** in audit-action.ts:101 — `fixStories &&` always true at that point. Simplified to `else`.\n    22→- **MEDIUM: NFR9 violation** — onboard.test.ts at 325 lines, compacted to 230.\n    23→- **MEDIUM: Branch coverage gap** — missing test for `skipped: true` path. Added, now 100%.\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed): console.log in audit-action.ts:111** — established codebase pattern, needs new `raw()` output utility to fix properly.\n    25→- **LOW (not fixed): formatAuditJson() is pass-through no-op** — exists for symmetry only.\n    26→- **Coverage: 96.97% overall, all 119 files above 80% floor, 2783 tests pass**\n    27→\n    28→### 3-3-onboard-alias — verify (2026-03-21T05:10Z)\n    29→\n    30→- All 8 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n    31→- Observability gaps: no structured log events emitted for any audit/onboard CLI interaction\n    32→- Pre-existing test failure in run-helpers.test.ts (--live flag test) had to be fixed before verification could proceed — not related to this story\n    33→\n    34→### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — create-story (2026-03-21T05:14Z)\n    35→\n    36→- Ambiguity: rules markdown as code vs documentation — chose hardcoded rules with markdown as reference docs\n    37→- Expanded ACs from 4 (epic) to 10 to cover each rule category individually\n    38→- Risk: regex-based validation may produce false positives for complex Dockerfiles\n    39→- `patches/infra/` directory doesn't exist yet — first file created there\n    40→\n    41→### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — dev-story (2026-03-21T05:22Z)\n    42→\n    43→- **Branch coverage at 87.5%** — The `line !== undefined` conditional in `dfGap()` helper has one branch not fully covered. Cosmetic; both paths exercised indirectly.\n    44→- **Verification tools check has potential false positives** — Regex checks for tool names anywhere in apt-get/apk lines. Matches story's stated approach: \"False positives are acceptable.\"\n    45→- **Dual file reads in checkInfrastructure** — Dockerfile read once for precondition checks, then again by `validateDockerfile()`. Intentional for backward-compatible error messages but redundant.\n    46→\n    47→### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — code-review (2026-03-21T05:32Z)\n    48→\n    49→- **HIGH: Operator precedence ambiguity** in `checkVerificationTools` — parentheses missing around `&&`/`||` chains. Fixed.\n    50→- **MEDIUM: Redundant double-read** of Dockerfile in `checkInfrastructure` — removed, delegated to `validateDockerfile`. Fixed.\n    51→- **MEDIUM: `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown` flag patterns** — regex updated. Fixed.\n    52→- **MEDIUM: No test for `COPY --from=` binary install pattern** — test added. Fixed.\n    53→- **LOW (not fixed): `checkVerificationTools` loose matching** — `content.includes(tool)` matches anywhere in file. Acceptable per story design.\n    54→- **LOW (not fixed): `checkBinaryOnPath` has no line number** — inconsistent with other checks but not a bug.\n    55→- **Coverage: 96.99% overall, 2817 tests, all 120 files above 80% floor**\n    56→\n    57→### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — verify (2026-03-21T05:35Z)\n    58→\n    59→- 9/10 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n    60→- **AC10 FAIL:** `validateDockerfile()` warnings stored in `DockerfileValidationResult.warnings[]` but not propagated by `checkInfrastructure()` to audit output. Fixed by adding warning-to-gap propagation in dimensions.ts. Test added (2820 tests pass). Story returned to `verifying` for re-verification in next session.\n    61→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"44e99ebb-e385-42dc-a684-d204e4d10303","uuid":"29db17bd-c4a2-4859-8989-6422ce5652f9","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:44:00.602Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n\n---\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — create-story (2026-03-21T04:24Z)\n\n- **Previous sprint file collision:** An existing `3-3-bmad-parser-story-bridge-command.md` exists from a previous sprint's Epic 3. No conflict since new file uses `3-3-onboard-alias.md`.\n- **Ambiguous AC3:** Epic says `codeharness onboard scan` should map to \"equivalent audit subcommand,\" but audit has no subcommands. Interpreted as deprecation warning + base audit run.\n- **Risk: Old exports removal.** `onboard.ts` exports `getLastScanResult()`, `getLastCoverageResult()`, `getLastAuditResult()`, and `resetLastScanResult()`. Need to verify no external consumers before removing.\n- **Risk: `onboard epic` subcommand has no audit equivalent.** Dropping silently may surprise users.\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — dev-story (2026-03-21T04:31Z)\n\n- **audit-action.ts branch coverage 95.83%:** Two uncovered branches (lines 96, 101) in JSON fix output formatting. Covered by audit.test.ts but not onboard.test.ts — redundant since both delegate to same handler.\n- **Test file size:** onboard.test.ts is 325 lines vs estimated 100-150. Consistent with project norms (audit.test.ts is 407 lines).\n- **console.log in shared handler:** audit-action.ts line 107 uses console.log directly. Story says \"Do NOT use console.log directly\" but formatAuditHuman() returns pre-formatted strings — wrapping in ok()/info() would double-prefix.\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — code-review (2026-03-21T04:38Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Unsafe double type assertion** in audit-action.ts:86 — `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` bypassed type safety. Fixed with spread operator.\n- **MEDIUM: Dead branch guard** in audit-action.ts:101 — `fixStories &&` always true at that point. Simplified to `else`.\n- **MEDIUM: NFR9 violation** — onboard.test.ts at 325 lines, compacted to 230.\n- **MEDIUM: Branch coverage gap** — missing test for `skipped: true` path. Added, now 100%.\n- **LOW (not fixed): console.log in audit-action.ts:111** — established codebase pattern, needs new `raw()` output utility to fix properly.\n- **LOW (not fixed): formatAuditJson() is pass-through no-op** — exists for symmetry only.\n- **Coverage: 96.97% overall, all 119 files above 80% floor, 2783 tests pass**\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — verify (2026-03-21T05:10Z)\n\n- All 8 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n- Observability gaps: no structured log events emitted for any audit/onboard CLI interaction\n- Pre-existing test failure in run-helpers.test.ts (--live flag test) had to be fixed before verification could proceed — not related to this story\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — create-story (2026-03-21T05:14Z)\n\n- Ambiguity: rules markdown as code vs documentation — chose hardcoded rules with markdown as reference docs\n- Expanded ACs from 4 (epic) to 10 to cover each rule category individually\n- Risk: regex-based validation may produce false positives for complex Dockerfiles\n- `patches/infra/` directory doesn't exist yet — first file created there\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — dev-story (2026-03-21T05:22Z)\n\n- **Branch coverage at 87.5%** — The `line !== undefined` conditional in `dfGap()` helper has one branch not fully covered. Cosmetic; both paths exercised indirectly.\n- **Verification tools check has potential false positives** — Regex checks for tool names anywhere in apt-get/apk lines. Matches story's stated approach: \"False positives are acceptable.\"\n- **Dual file reads in checkInfrastructure** — Dockerfile read once for precondition checks, then again by `validateDockerfile()`. Intentional for backward-compatible error messages but redundant.\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — code-review (2026-03-21T05:32Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Operator precedence ambiguity** in `checkVerificationTools` — parentheses missing around `&&`/`||` chains. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: Redundant double-read** of Dockerfile in `checkInfrastructure` — removed, delegated to `validateDockerfile`. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown` flag patterns** — regex updated. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for `COPY --from=` binary install pattern** — test added. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `checkVerificationTools` loose matching** — `content.includes(tool)` matches anywhere in file. Acceptable per story design.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `checkBinaryOnPath` has no line number** — inconsistent with other checks but not a bug.\n- **Coverage: 96.99% overall, 2817 tests, all 120 files above 80% floor**\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — verify (2026-03-21T05:35Z)\n\n- 9/10 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n- **AC10 FAIL:** `validateDockerfile()` warnings stored in `DockerfileValidationResult.warnings[]` but not propagated by `checkInfrastructure()` to audit output. Fixed by adding warning-to-gap propagation in dimensions.ts. Test added (2820 tests pass). Story returned to `verifying` for re-verification in next session.\n","numLines":61,"startLine":1,"totalLines":61}}}
