{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U51egJEezTQNsm11J8ruuw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 4.2: Dockerfile Template & Dev Integration\n     2→\n     3→Status: ready-for-dev\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer,\n    10→I want a Dockerfile template generated at init and a dev workflow prompt for dependency changes,\n    11→so that the Dockerfile stays correct as the project evolves.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **Given** `codeharness init` detects a Node.js project (package.json exists), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists in the project root, **Then** a `Dockerfile` is generated from `templates/Dockerfile.verify` with pinned FROM, npm pack + install, verification tools (curl, jq), cache cleanup, and non-root USER. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. **Given** `codeharness init` detects a Python project (requirements.txt or pyproject.toml exists), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists in the project root, **Then** a `Dockerfile` is generated with pinned python base, pip install, verification tools, cache cleanup, and non-root USER. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **Given** `codeharness init` cannot detect the project type (no package.json, requirements.txt, or pyproject.toml), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists, **Then** a generic `Dockerfile` is generated from `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` with basic verification tools. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. **Given** `codeharness init` runs and a `Dockerfile` already exists in the project root, **When** init completes, **Then** the existing Dockerfile is NOT overwritten, and init logs: \"Dockerfile already exists -- skipping template generation.\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. **Given** a Dockerfile generated by `codeharness init`, **When** `validateDockerfile()` from Story 4.1 is run against it, **Then** it passes all 6 rule categories with zero gaps. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. **Given** `patches/dev/enforcement.md` exists, **When** read after this story is implemented, **Then** it includes a section instructing the dev agent: \"If this story adds a new runtime dependency, check whether the Dockerfile needs updating (e.g., new system package, new binary on PATH).\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. **Given** the generated Dockerfile is committed to git, **When** a developer inspects it, **Then** it has comments explaining each section (base image, tools, binary install, cleanup, user) so the developer understands what to maintain. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→8. **Given** `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)` is called, **When** it returns, **Then** it returns `Result<{ path: string; stack: string }>` following the project's Result<T> pattern. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→9. **Given** `generateDockerfileTemplate()` is exported from `src/modules/infra/index.ts`, **When** imported by other modules, **Then** it is available via the barrel export only (not direct file import). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→10. **Given** `codeharness init` generates a Dockerfile, **When** the init result is returned, **Then** `InitResult` includes a `dockerfile` field indicating the template was generated (e.g., `{ generated: true, stack: 'nodejs' }`). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→\n    26→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    27→\n    28→- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #7, #8)\n    29→  - [ ] 1.1: Define `DockerfileTemplateResult` interface: `{ path: string; stack: string }`\n    30→  - [ ] 1.2: `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir: string, stack: string | null): Result<DockerfileTemplateResult>` — checks for existing Dockerfile, selects template by stack, writes to project root\n    31→  - [ ] 1.3: Node.js template content: pinned `FROM node:22-slim`, `ARG TARBALL`, apt-get install curl/jq, `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`, `npm install -g` from tarball, `USER node`, section comments\n    32→  - [ ] 1.4: Python template content: pinned `FROM python:3.12-slim`, apt-get install curl/jq, pip install from wheel/sdist, `pip cache purge`, `USER nobody`, section comments\n    33→  - [ ] 1.5: Generic template content: pinned `FROM node:22-slim`, basic tools (bash, curl, jq, git), cache cleanup, section comments\n    34→  - [ ] 1.6: Return `fail('Dockerfile already exists')` when Dockerfile is present (caller handles messaging)\n    35→  - [ ] 1.7: Each generated Dockerfile includes inline comments explaining sections\n    36→\n    37→- [ ] Task 2: Export from barrel `src/modules/infra/index.ts` (AC: #9)\n    38→  - [ ] 2.1: Export `generateDockerfileTemplate` function from barrel\n    39→  - [ ] 2.2: Export `DockerfileTemplateResult` type from barrel\n    40→\n    41→- [ ] Task 3: Integrate into `codeharness init` flow (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #10)\n    42→  - [ ] 3.1: In `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`, after stack detection and before Docker setup, call `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)`\n    43→  - [ ] 3.2: If Dockerfile already exists, log info message: \"Dockerfile already exists -- skipping template generation.\"\n    44→  - [ ] 3.3: If template generated successfully, log info message: \"Generated Dockerfile for {stack} project.\"\n    45→  - [ ] 3.4: Add `dockerfile?: { generated: boolean; stack: string }` field to `InitResult` type in `src/modules/infra/types.ts`\n    46→  - [ ] 3.5: Populate `InitResult.dockerfile` based on template generation outcome\n    47→\n    48→- [ ] Task 4: Update dev workflow patch (AC: #6)\n    49→  - [ ] 4.1: Add a `### Dockerfile Maintenance` section to `patches/dev/enforcement.md` instructing the dev agent to check Dockerfile updates when new runtime dependencies are added\n    50→  - [ ] 4.2: Include specific guidance: check if new system packages, binaries, or Python packages need to be added to the Dockerfile\n    51→\n    52→- [ ] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: all)\n    53→  - [ ] 5.1: Create `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`:\n    54→    - Test Node.js stack generates Dockerfile with correct content (pinned FROM, npm install -g, curl, jq, USER node, cache cleanup)\n    55→    - Test Python stack generates Dockerfile with correct content (pinned FROM, pip install, curl, jq, USER nobody, cache cleanup)\n    56→    - Test null/unknown stack generates generic Dockerfile\n    57→    - Test existing Dockerfile returns fail result (not overwritten)\n    58→    - Test generated Dockerfile passes `validateDockerfile()` with zero gaps\n    59→    - Test generated files have inline comments\n    60→    - Test Result<T> return type\n    61→  - [ ] 5.2: Update `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` (if exists) or add tests for init integration:\n    62→    - Test init calls generateDockerfileTemplate when no Dockerfile exists\n    63→    - Test init skips template generation when Dockerfile exists\n    64→    - Test InitResult includes dockerfile field\n    65→  - [ ] 5.3: Mock all I/O: filesystem (writeFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync)\n    66→  - [ ] 5.4: Target 100% coverage on new files\n    67→\n    68→- [ ] Task 6: Integration verification (AC: all)\n    69→  - [ ] 6.1: `npm run build` — verify tsup compiles new files\n    70→  - [ ] 6.2: `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n    71→  - [ ] 6.3: Verify module boundaries: only barrel `index.ts` exports public API\n    72→  - [ ] 6.4: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9)\n    73→  - [ ] 6.5: Verify generated Dockerfile passes `validateDockerfile()` end-to-end (AC #5)\n    74→\n    75→## Dev Notes\n    76→\n    77→### Architecture References\n    78→\n    79→This story implements FR22 (Dockerfile template based on project type) and FR25 (dev workflow prompts Dockerfile update on new deps). It builds on Story 4.1's `validateDockerfile()` and the existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` files. Architecture Decision 5 (Rules as Markdown) establishes the pattern.\n    80→\n    81→### Key Implementation Details\n    82→\n    83→**Template generation, not copying:** `generateDockerfileTemplate()` does NOT simply copy `templates/Dockerfile.verify` into the project. It generates a new Dockerfile based on detected stack type with appropriate content. The existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` is codeharness's own verification Dockerfile — the new template is for the user's project.\n    84→\n    85→**Stack detection reuse:** Use `detectStack()` from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` which already returns `'nodejs' | 'python' | null`. No new detection logic needed.\n    86→\n    87→**Idempotency (AC #4):** If a Dockerfile already exists, `generateDockerfileTemplate()` returns `fail('Dockerfile already exists')`. The init orchestrator handles this gracefully — log a skip message, continue init. This preserves the project's existing Dockerfile.\n    88→\n    89→**Compliance by construction (AC #5):** The generated templates MUST pass all 6 rule categories from Story 4.1. This is a design constraint — if the template doesn't pass validation, the template is buggy. Test this explicitly.\n    90→\n    91→**Dev workflow patch (AC #6):** Update `patches/dev/enforcement.md` with a Dockerfile maintenance section. This is a patch file — the dev agent reads it during implementation. No code execution, just documentation that guides agent behavior.\n    92→\n    93→**Comments in generated Dockerfiles (AC #7):** Each section of the generated Dockerfile gets a comment explaining its purpose. This helps developers maintain the Dockerfile when codeharness isn't involved.\n    94→\n    95→### Node.js Template Structure\n    96→\n    97→```dockerfile\n    98→# Base image — pinned version for reproducibility\n    99→FROM node:22-slim\n   100→\n   101→ARG TARBALL=package.tgz\n   102→\n   103→# System utilities for verification\n   104→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n   105→    curl \\\n   106→    jq \\\n   107→  && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   108→\n   109→# Install project from tarball (black-box: no source code)\n   110→COPY ${TARBALL} /tmp/${TARBALL}\n   111→RUN npm install -g /tmp/${TARBALL} && rm /tmp/${TARBALL}\n   112→\n   113→# Run as non-root user\n   114→USER node\n   115→\n   116→WORKDIR /workspace\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→### Python Template Structure\n   120→\n   121→```dockerfile\n   122→# Base image — pinned version for reproducibility\n   123→FROM python:3.12-slim\n   124→\n   125→# System utilities for verification\n   126→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n   127→    curl \\\n   128→    jq \\\n   129→  && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   130→\n   131→# Install project from wheel or sdist\n   132→COPY dist/ /tmp/dist/\n   133→RUN pip install /tmp/dist/*.whl && rm -rf /tmp/dist/ && pip cache purge\n   134→\n   135→# Run as non-root user\n   136→USER nobody\n   137→\n   138→WORKDIR /workspace\n   139→```\n   140→\n   141→### Existing Code to Reuse\n   142→\n   143→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` — `validateDockerfile()` to verify generated templates pass all rules\n   144→- `src/modules/infra/index.ts` — barrel file to export new `generateDockerfileTemplate`\n   145→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — init orchestrator to integrate template generation\n   146→- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — `InitResult` type to extend with `dockerfile` field\n   147→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — `detectStack()` for project type detection\n   148→- `src/types/result.ts` — `Result<T>`, `ok()`, `fail()` for return types\n   149→- `templates/Dockerfile.verify` — reference for Node.js template content (codeharness's own)\n   150→- `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` — reference for generic template content\n   151→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — dev workflow patch to update with Dockerfile maintenance\n   152→\n   153→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   154→\n   155→- No `docker build` execution — template generation is file I/O only\n   156→- No Dockerfile linting beyond `validateDockerfile()` — Story 4.1 handles validation\n   157→- No auto-updating of Dockerfiles when dependencies change — the dev workflow _prompts_ the agent, it doesn't auto-modify\n   158→- No multi-stage build templates — keep it simple, single-stage for now\n   159→- No CI/CD Dockerfile generation — this is for verification Dockerfiles only\n   160→\n   161→### Dependencies\n   162→\n   163→- **Depends on:** Story 4.1 (dockerfile-validator, `validateDockerfile()`) — DONE\n   164→- **Depended on by:** None in current sprint\n   165→\n   166→### File Size Constraint\n   167→\n   168→Each new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9.\n   169→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — ~80-120 lines (template generation)\n   170→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — ~150-250 lines (tests)\n   171→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — modification only, adding ~10 lines\n   172→\n   173→### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 4.1 Dockerfile Validator)\n   174→\n   175→- **`validateDockerfile()` checks 6 rule categories.** Generated templates must pass all 6.\n   176→- **`DockerfileGap` has `{ rule, description, suggestedFix, line? }`.** Use `validateDockerfile()` in tests to verify templates.\n   177→- **`loadRules()` falls back to hardcoded defaults.** Templates don't need `patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md` to validate — defaults suffice.\n   178→- **Barrel imports only.** Import from `../infra/index.js`, not from `dockerfile-template.js` directly.\n   179→- **The `Result<T>` pattern** uses `ok()` and `fail()` from `src/types/result.ts`.\n   180→\n   181→### Git Intelligence\n   182→\n   183→Recent commits show Story 4.1 complete. The project uses:\n   184→- Commander for CLI commands\n   185→- `Result<T>` discriminated union for error handling\n   186→- tsup for building\n   187→- Vitest for testing\n   188→- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) for module boundaries\n   189→- `detectStack()` returns `'nodejs' | 'python' | null`\n   190→- Init orchestrator in `init-project.ts` composes sub-steps sequentially\n   191→- `InitResult` type in `types.ts` structures the init output\n   192→\n   193→### References\n   194→\n   195→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 5] — Rules as Markdown, validator approach\n   196→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 4.2] — Acceptance criteria\n   197→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR22] — Dockerfile template based on project type\n   198→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR25] — Dev workflow prompts Dockerfile update\n   199→- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts] — Validator to verify generated templates\n   200→- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts] — Init orchestrator to integrate template generation\n   201→- [Source: templates/Dockerfile.verify] — Reference Node.js verification Dockerfile\n   202→\n   203→### Project Structure Notes\n   204→\n   205→- New files: `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts`, `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`\n   206→- Modified files: `src/modules/infra/index.ts` (add barrel export), `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` (integrate template generation), `src/modules/infra/types.ts` (extend InitResult), `patches/dev/enforcement.md` (add Dockerfile maintenance section)\n   207→- Module follows existing conventions: barrel exports, Result<T> returns, <300 line files\n   208→\n   209→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   210→## Verification Requirements\n   211→\n   212→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.proof.md`)\n   213→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   214→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   215→\n   216→## Documentation Requirements\n   217→\n   218→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/infra/AGENTS.md)\n   219→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.md`\n   220→\n   221→## Testing Requirements\n   222→\n   223→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   224→- [ ] All I/O mocked (filesystem, subprocess, HTTP)\n   225→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   226→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   227→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MfXggqZdC7KtDFQHUh8K9V","session_id":"44e99ebb-e385-42dc-a684-d204e4d10303","uuid":"21bf9e60-a6d3-4cba-875b-cc43eba10f10","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:44:29.190Z"}
