{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0169vTiL2X15XS1oGwFMvuz9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in order. Here is the summary.\n\n---\n\n## Code Review: Story 4.2 — Dockerfile Template & Dev Integration\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.md`\n**Status updated:** `review` -> `verifying`\n**Tests:** 2845 passed (0 failed), up from 2842 (+3 new error-handling tests)\n**Coverage:** 96.98% overall, all 121 files above 80% floor\n**Build:** passes\n\n### Issues Found and Fixed\n\n**HIGH — Unhandled `writeFileSync` exception (FIXED)**\n`src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` line 106: `writeFileSync` was called without try/catch. If the write fails (permission denied, disk full), the function throws instead of returning `fail()`. This violates the project's \"never throws\" contract documented in AGENTS.md. Added try/catch that returns `fail('Failed to write Dockerfile: ...')`.\n\n**MEDIUM — Missing input validation for `projectDir` (FIXED)**\n`src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts`: No guard against empty/falsy `projectDir`. Added early return `fail('projectDir is required')` for empty string.\n\n**MEDIUM — Test mock leak between describe blocks (FIXED)**\n`src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` line 17: Used `vi.clearAllMocks()` which clears call history but does NOT reset mock implementations. After the new error-handling tests set throwing mocks, subsequent tests inherited those implementations. Changed to `vi.resetAllMocks()`.\n\n### Files Modified\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — added try/catch around writeFileSync, added projectDir validation\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — added 3 error-handling tests, fixed mock reset strategy\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.md` — status changed to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: `writeFileSync` throws unhandled exception on I/O failure — violates Result<T> contract. Fixed with try/catch.\n- MEDIUM: No input validation on `projectDir` — falsy values produce garbage paths. Fixed with guard clause.\n- MEDIUM: `vi.clearAllMocks()` doesn't reset mock implementations, causing test pollution. Fixed by switching to `vi.resetAllMocks()`.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- The `resolvedStack` variable is redundant — it always equals `stack` for nodejs/python, or `'generic'` otherwise. Could simplify by setting `resolvedStack` directly in each branch without a separate variable, but the current code is clear enough.\n- Template functions (`nodejsTemplate`, `pythonTemplate`, `genericTemplate`) are private and untestable independently. Only testable through the public function. Acceptable for this module size.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No test for `generateDockerfileTemplate` being called during `initProject` integration (init-project.test.ts does not verify the dockerfile field in InitResult). This is documented in the story as \"Init integration is covered by existing init-project.test.ts\" but the existing init tests predate story 4.2 and don't assert on the `dockerfile` field.\n- Missing Showboat proof document at `docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.proof.md` — exec-plan exists but no proof doc.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The implementation follows established patterns (Result<T>, barrel exports, orchestrator composition).\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab1133e0af5f393ac (use SendMessage with to: 'ab1133e0af5f393ac' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 66889\ntool_uses: 56\nduration_ms: 268048</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session