{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C1s3ZDNAjLgxRgQgBcUW4i","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 4.2: Dockerfile Template & Dev Integration\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer,\n    10→I want a Dockerfile template generated at init and a dev workflow prompt for dependency changes,\n    11→so that the Dockerfile stays correct as the project evolves.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **Given** `codeharness init` detects a Node.js project (package.json exists), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists in the project root, **Then** a `Dockerfile` is generated from `templates/Dockerfile.verify` with pinned FROM, npm pack + install, verification tools (curl, jq), cache cleanup, and non-root USER. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. **Given** `codeharness init` detects a Python project (requirements.txt or pyproject.toml exists), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists in the project root, **Then** a `Dockerfile` is generated with pinned python base, pip install, verification tools, cache cleanup, and non-root USER. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **Given** `codeharness init` cannot detect the project type (no package.json, requirements.txt, or pyproject.toml), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists, **Then** a generic `Dockerfile` is generated from `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` with basic verification tools. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. **Given** `codeharness init` runs and a `Dockerfile` already exists in the project root, **When** init completes, **Then** the existing Dockerfile is NOT overwritten, and init logs: \"Dockerfile already exists -- skipping template generation.\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. **Given** a Dockerfile generated by `codeharness init`, **When** `validateDockerfile()` from Story 4.1 is run against it, **Then** it passes all 6 rule categories with zero gaps. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. **Given** `patches/dev/enforcement.md` exists, **When** read after this story is implemented, **Then** it includes a section instructing the dev agent: \"If this story adds a new runtime dependency, check whether the Dockerfile needs updating (e.g., new system package, new binary on PATH).\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. **Given** the generated Dockerfile is committed to git, **When** a developer inspects it, **Then** it has comments explaining each section (base image, tools, binary install, cleanup, user) so the developer understands what to maintain. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→8. **Given** `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)` is called, **When** it returns, **Then** it returns `Result<{ path: string; stack: string }>` following the project's Result<T> pattern. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→9. **Given** `generateDockerfileTemplate()` is exported from `src/modules/infra/index.ts`, **When** imported by other modules, **Then** it is available via the barrel export only (not direct file import). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→10. **Given** `codeharness init` generates a Dockerfile, **When** the init result is returned, **Then** `InitResult` includes a `dockerfile` field indicating the template was generated (e.g., `{ generated: true, stack: 'nodejs' }`). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→\n    26→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    27→\n    28→- [x] Task 1: Create `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #7, #8)\n    29→  - [x] 1.1: Define `DockerfileTemplateResult` interface: `{ path: string; stack: string }`\n    30→  - [x] 1.2: `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir: string, stack: string | null): Result<DockerfileTemplateResult>` — checks for existing Dockerfile, selects template by stack, writes to project root\n    31→  - [x] 1.3: Node.js template content: pinned `FROM node:22-slim`, `ARG TARBALL`, apt-get install curl/jq, `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`, `npm install -g` from tarball, `USER node`, section comments\n    32→  - [x] 1.4: Python template content: pinned `FROM python:3.12-slim`, apt-get install curl/jq, pip install from wheel/sdist, `pip cache purge`, `USER nobody`, section comments\n    33→  - [x] 1.5: Generic template content: pinned `FROM node:22-slim`, basic tools (bash, curl, jq, git), cache cleanup, section comments\n    34→  - [x] 1.6: Return `fail('Dockerfile already exists')` when Dockerfile is present (caller handles messaging)\n    35→  - [x] 1.7: Each generated Dockerfile includes inline comments explaining sections\n    36→\n    37→- [x] Task 2: Export from barrel `src/modules/infra/index.ts` (AC: #9)\n    38→  - [x] 2.1: Export `generateDockerfileTemplate` function from barrel\n    39→  - [x] 2.2: Export `DockerfileTemplateResult` type from barrel\n    40→\n    41→- [x] Task 3: Integrate into `codeharness init` flow (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #10)\n    42→  - [x] 3.1: In `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`, after stack detection and before Docker setup, call `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)`\n    43→  - [x] 3.2: If Dockerfile already exists, log info message: \"Dockerfile already exists -- skipping template generation.\"\n    44→  - [x] 3.3: If template generated successfully, log info message: \"Generated Dockerfile for {stack} project.\"\n    45→  - [x] 3.4: Add `dockerfile?: { generated: boolean; stack: string }` field to `InitResult` type in `src/modules/infra/types.ts`\n    46→  - [x] 3.5: Populate `InitResult.dockerfile` based on template generation outcome\n    47→\n    48→- [x] Task 4: Update dev workflow patch (AC: #6)\n    49→  - [x] 4.1: Add a `### Dockerfile Maintenance` section to `patches/dev/enforcement.md` instructing the dev agent to check Dockerfile updates when new runtime dependencies are added\n    50→  - [x] 4.2: Include specific guidance: check if new system packages, binaries, or Python packages need to be added to the Dockerfile\n    51→\n    52→- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: all)\n    53→  - [x] 5.1: Create `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`:\n    54→    - Test Node.js stack generates Dockerfile with correct content (pinned FROM, npm install -g, curl, jq, USER node, cache cleanup)\n    55→    - Test Python stack generates Dockerfile with correct content (pinned FROM, pip install, curl, jq, USER nobody, cache cleanup)\n    56→    - Test null/unknown stack generates generic Dockerfile\n    57→    - Test existing Dockerfile returns fail result (not overwritten)\n    58→    - Test generated Dockerfile passes `validateDockerfile()` with zero gaps\n    59→    - Test generated files have inline comments\n    60→    - Test Result<T> return type\n    61→  - [x] 5.2: Init integration is covered by existing init-project.test.ts (template generation is called automatically via the init orchestrator; direct unit tests verify the function independently)\n    62→  - [x] 5.3: Mock all I/O: filesystem (writeFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync)\n    63→  - [x] 5.4: Target 100% coverage on new files\n    64→\n    65→- [x] Task 6: Integration verification (AC: all)\n    66→  - [x] 6.1: `npm run build` — verify tsup compiles new files\n    67→  - [x] 6.2: `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions (2842 tests, 110 files)\n    68→  - [x] 6.3: Verify module boundaries: only barrel `index.ts` exports public API\n    69→  - [x] 6.4: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9) — template: 109 lines, tests: 294 lines\n    70→  - [x] 6.5: Verify generated Dockerfile passes `validateDockerfile()` end-to-end (AC #5)\n    71→\n    72→## Dev Notes\n    73→\n    74→### Architecture References\n    75→\n    76→This story implements FR22 (Dockerfile template based on project type) and FR25 (dev workflow prompts Dockerfile update on new deps). It builds on Story 4.1's `validateDockerfile()` and the existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` files. Architecture Decision 5 (Rules as Markdown) establishes the pattern.\n    77→\n    78→### Key Implementation Details\n    79→\n    80→**Template generation, not copying:** `generateDockerfileTemplate()` does NOT simply copy `templates/Dockerfile.verify` into the project. It generates a new Dockerfile based on detected stack type with appropriate content. The existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` is codeharness's own verification Dockerfile — the new template is for the user's project.\n    81→\n    82→**Stack detection reuse:** Use `detectStack()` from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` which already returns `'nodejs' | 'python' | null`. No new detection logic needed.\n    83→\n    84→**Idempotency (AC #4):** If a Dockerfile already exists, `generateDockerfileTemplate()` returns `fail('Dockerfile already exists')`. The init orchestrator handles this gracefully — log a skip message, continue init. This preserves the project's existing Dockerfile.\n    85→\n    86→**Compliance by construction (AC #5):** The generated templates MUST pass all 6 rule categories from Story 4.1. This is a design constraint — if the template doesn't pass validation, the template is buggy. Test this explicitly.\n    87→\n    88→**Dev workflow patch (AC #6):** Update `patches/dev/enforcement.md` with a Dockerfile maintenance section. This is a patch file — the dev agent reads it during implementation. No code execution, just documentation that guides agent behavior.\n    89→\n    90→**Comments in generated Dockerfiles (AC #7):** Each section of the generated Dockerfile gets a comment explaining its purpose. This helps developers maintain the Dockerfile when codeharness isn't involved.\n    91→\n    92→### Node.js Template Structure\n    93→\n    94→```dockerfile\n    95→# Base image — pinned version for reproducibility\n    96→FROM node:22-slim\n    97→\n    98→ARG TARBALL=package.tgz\n    99→\n   100→# System utilities for verification\n   101→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n   102→    curl \\\n   103→    jq \\\n   104→  && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   105→\n   106→# Install project from tarball (black-box: no source code)\n   107→COPY ${TARBALL} /tmp/${TARBALL}\n   108→RUN npm install -g /tmp/${TARBALL} && rm /tmp/${TARBALL}\n   109→\n   110→# Run as non-root user\n   111→USER node\n   112→\n   113→WORKDIR /workspace\n   114→```\n   115→\n   116→### Python Template Structure\n   117→\n   118→```dockerfile\n   119→# Base image — pinned version for reproducibility\n   120→FROM python:3.12-slim\n   121→\n   122→# System utilities for verification\n   123→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n   124→    curl \\\n   125→    jq \\\n   126→  && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   127→\n   128→# Install project from wheel or sdist\n   129→COPY dist/ /tmp/dist/\n   130→RUN pip install /tmp/dist/*.whl && rm -rf /tmp/dist/ && pip cache purge\n   131→\n   132→# Run as non-root user\n   133→USER nobody\n   134→\n   135→WORKDIR /workspace\n   136→```\n   137→\n   138→### Existing Code to Reuse\n   139→\n   140→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` — `validateDockerfile()` to verify generated templates pass all rules\n   141→- `src/modules/infra/index.ts` — barrel file to export new `generateDockerfileTemplate`\n   142→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — init orchestrator to integrate template generation\n   143→- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — `InitResult` type to extend with `dockerfile` field\n   144→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — `detectStack()` for project type detection\n   145→- `src/types/result.ts` — `Result<T>`, `ok()`, `fail()` for return types\n   146→- `templates/Dockerfile.verify` — reference for Node.js template content (codeharness's own)\n   147→- `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` — reference for generic template content\n   148→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — dev workflow patch to update with Dockerfile maintenance\n   149→\n   150→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   151→\n   152→- No `docker build` execution — template generation is file I/O only\n   153→- No Dockerfile linting beyond `validateDockerfile()` — Story 4.1 handles validation\n   154→- No auto-updating of Dockerfiles when dependencies change — the dev workflow _prompts_ the agent, it doesn't auto-modify\n   155→- No multi-stage build templates — keep it simple, single-stage for now\n   156→- No CI/CD Dockerfile generation — this is for verification Dockerfiles only\n   157→\n   158→### Dependencies\n   159→\n   160→- **Depends on:** Story 4.1 (dockerfile-validator, `validateDockerfile()`) — DONE\n   161→- **Depended on by:** None in current sprint\n   162→\n   163→### File Size Constraint\n   164→\n   165→Each new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9.\n   166→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — ~80-120 lines (template generation)\n   167→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — ~150-250 lines (tests)\n   168→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — modification only, adding ~10 lines\n   169→\n   170→### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 4.1 Dockerfile Validator)\n   171→\n   172→- **`validateDockerfile()` checks 6 rule categories.** Generated templates must pass all 6.\n   173→- **`DockerfileGap` has `{ rule, description, suggestedFix, line? }`.** Use `validateDockerfile()` in tests to verify templates.\n   174→- **`loadRules()` falls back to hardcoded defaults.** Templates don't need `patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md` to validate — defaults suffice.\n   175→- **Barrel imports only.** Import from `../infra/index.js`, not from `dockerfile-template.js` directly.\n   176→- **The `Result<T>` pattern** uses `ok()` and `fail()` from `src/types/result.ts`.\n   177→\n   178→### Git Intelligence\n   179→\n   180→Recent commits show Story 4.1 complete. The project uses:\n   181→- Commander for CLI commands\n   182→- `Result<T>` discriminated union for error handling\n   183→- tsup for building\n   184→- Vitest for testing\n   185→- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) for module boundaries\n   186→- `detectStack()` returns `'nodejs' | 'python' | null`\n   187→- Init orchestrator in `init-project.ts` composes sub-steps sequentially\n   188→- `InitResult` type in `types.ts` structures the init output\n   189→\n   190→### References\n   191→\n   192→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 5] — Rules as Markdown, validator approach\n   193→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 4.2] — Acceptance criteria\n   194→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR22] — Dockerfile template based on project type\n   195→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR25] — Dev workflow prompts Dockerfile update\n   196→- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts] — Validator to verify generated templates\n   197→- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts] — Init orchestrator to integrate template generation\n   198→- [Source: templates/Dockerfile.verify] — Reference Node.js verification Dockerfile\n   199→\n   200→### Project Structure Notes\n   201→\n   202→- New files: `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts`, `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`\n   203→- Modified files: `src/modules/infra/index.ts` (add barrel export), `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` (integrate template generation), `src/modules/infra/types.ts` (extend InitResult), `patches/dev/enforcement.md` (add Dockerfile maintenance section)\n   204→- Module follows existing conventions: barrel exports, Result<T> returns, <300 line files\n   205→\n   206→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   207→## Verification Requirements\n   208→\n   209→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.proof.md`)\n   210→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   211→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   212→\n   213→## Documentation Requirements\n   214→\n   215→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/infra/AGENTS.md)\n   216→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.md`\n   217→\n   218→## Testing Requirements\n   219→\n   220→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   221→- [ ] All I/O mocked (filesystem, subprocess, HTTP)\n   222→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   223→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   224→\n   225→## Dev Agent Record\n   226→\n   227→### Implementation Notes\n   228→\n   229→- Templates use single-line `apt-get install` format because `validateDockerfile()` checks each line independently for tool presence on install lines. Multi-line continuation (`\\`) splits across lines and the validator doesn't join them.\n   230→- Generic template uses `npm install -g placeholder` as a binary install placeholder to satisfy the binary-on-path rule. Users must replace this.\n   231→- Template generation is synchronous — only file I/O, no subprocess calls.\n   232→- All 3 template variants (nodejs, python, generic) pass all 6 rule categories with zero gaps, verified by dedicated test cases.\n   233→\n   234→### Completion Notes\n   235→\n   236→All 6 tasks complete. 22 new tests added in dockerfile-template.test.ts covering: template content for all 3 stacks, existing Dockerfile idempotency, Result<T> type contract, validateDockerfile() compliance, and inline comments. Full regression suite passes (2842 tests, 110 files). Build succeeds. No new dependencies added.\n   237→\n   238→## File List\n   239→\n   240→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — new\n   241→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — new\n   242→- `src/modules/infra/index.ts` — modified\n   243→- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — modified\n   244→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — modified\n   245→- `src/modules/infra/AGENTS.md` — modified\n   246→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — modified\n   247→- `docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.md` — new\n   248→\n   249→## Change Log\n   250→\n   251→- 2026-03-21: Implemented Story 4.2 — Dockerfile template generation for nodejs/python/generic stacks, integrated into init flow, updated dev enforcement patch with Dockerfile maintenance guidance, 22 unit tests added.\n   252→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"44e99ebb-e385-42dc-a684-d204e4d10303","uuid":"32062052-ebd4-4e63-8023-46f80b2a549f","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:55:59.709Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/codeharness-verify-4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration/story.md","content":"# Story 4.2: Dockerfile Template & Dev Integration\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want a Dockerfile template generated at init and a dev workflow prompt for dependency changes,\nso that the Dockerfile stays correct as the project evolves.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** `codeharness init` detects a Node.js project (package.json exists), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists in the project root, **Then** a `Dockerfile` is generated from `templates/Dockerfile.verify` with pinned FROM, npm pack + install, verification tools (curl, jq), cache cleanup, and non-root USER. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n2. **Given** `codeharness init` detects a Python project (requirements.txt or pyproject.toml exists), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists in the project root, **Then** a `Dockerfile` is generated with pinned python base, pip install, verification tools, cache cleanup, and non-root USER. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n3. **Given** `codeharness init` cannot detect the project type (no package.json, requirements.txt, or pyproject.toml), **When** no `Dockerfile` exists, **Then** a generic `Dockerfile` is generated from `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` with basic verification tools. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n4. **Given** `codeharness init` runs and a `Dockerfile` already exists in the project root, **When** init completes, **Then** the existing Dockerfile is NOT overwritten, and init logs: \"Dockerfile already exists -- skipping template generation.\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n5. **Given** a Dockerfile generated by `codeharness init`, **When** `validateDockerfile()` from Story 4.1 is run against it, **Then** it passes all 6 rule categories with zero gaps. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n6. **Given** `patches/dev/enforcement.md` exists, **When** read after this story is implemented, **Then** it includes a section instructing the dev agent: \"If this story adds a new runtime dependency, check whether the Dockerfile needs updating (e.g., new system package, new binary on PATH).\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n7. **Given** the generated Dockerfile is committed to git, **When** a developer inspects it, **Then** it has comments explaining each section (base image, tools, binary install, cleanup, user) so the developer understands what to maintain. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n8. **Given** `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)` is called, **When** it returns, **Then** it returns `Result<{ path: string; stack: string }>` following the project's Result<T> pattern. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n9. **Given** `generateDockerfileTemplate()` is exported from `src/modules/infra/index.ts`, **When** imported by other modules, **Then** it is available via the barrel export only (not direct file import). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n10. **Given** `codeharness init` generates a Dockerfile, **When** the init result is returned, **Then** `InitResult` includes a `dockerfile` field indicating the template was generated (e.g., `{ generated: true, stack: 'nodejs' }`). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Create `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #7, #8)\n  - [x] 1.1: Define `DockerfileTemplateResult` interface: `{ path: string; stack: string }`\n  - [x] 1.2: `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir: string, stack: string | null): Result<DockerfileTemplateResult>` — checks for existing Dockerfile, selects template by stack, writes to project root\n  - [x] 1.3: Node.js template content: pinned `FROM node:22-slim`, `ARG TARBALL`, apt-get install curl/jq, `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`, `npm install -g` from tarball, `USER node`, section comments\n  - [x] 1.4: Python template content: pinned `FROM python:3.12-slim`, apt-get install curl/jq, pip install from wheel/sdist, `pip cache purge`, `USER nobody`, section comments\n  - [x] 1.5: Generic template content: pinned `FROM node:22-slim`, basic tools (bash, curl, jq, git), cache cleanup, section comments\n  - [x] 1.6: Return `fail('Dockerfile already exists')` when Dockerfile is present (caller handles messaging)\n  - [x] 1.7: Each generated Dockerfile includes inline comments explaining sections\n\n- [x] Task 2: Export from barrel `src/modules/infra/index.ts` (AC: #9)\n  - [x] 2.1: Export `generateDockerfileTemplate` function from barrel\n  - [x] 2.2: Export `DockerfileTemplateResult` type from barrel\n\n- [x] Task 3: Integrate into `codeharness init` flow (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #10)\n  - [x] 3.1: In `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`, after stack detection and before Docker setup, call `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)`\n  - [x] 3.2: If Dockerfile already exists, log info message: \"Dockerfile already exists -- skipping template generation.\"\n  - [x] 3.3: If template generated successfully, log info message: \"Generated Dockerfile for {stack} project.\"\n  - [x] 3.4: Add `dockerfile?: { generated: boolean; stack: string }` field to `InitResult` type in `src/modules/infra/types.ts`\n  - [x] 3.5: Populate `InitResult.dockerfile` based on template generation outcome\n\n- [x] Task 4: Update dev workflow patch (AC: #6)\n  - [x] 4.1: Add a `### Dockerfile Maintenance` section to `patches/dev/enforcement.md` instructing the dev agent to check Dockerfile updates when new runtime dependencies are added\n  - [x] 4.2: Include specific guidance: check if new system packages, binaries, or Python packages need to be added to the Dockerfile\n\n- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: all)\n  - [x] 5.1: Create `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`:\n    - Test Node.js stack generates Dockerfile with correct content (pinned FROM, npm install -g, curl, jq, USER node, cache cleanup)\n    - Test Python stack generates Dockerfile with correct content (pinned FROM, pip install, curl, jq, USER nobody, cache cleanup)\n    - Test null/unknown stack generates generic Dockerfile\n    - Test existing Dockerfile returns fail result (not overwritten)\n    - Test generated Dockerfile passes `validateDockerfile()` with zero gaps\n    - Test generated files have inline comments\n    - Test Result<T> return type\n  - [x] 5.2: Init integration is covered by existing init-project.test.ts (template generation is called automatically via the init orchestrator; direct unit tests verify the function independently)\n  - [x] 5.3: Mock all I/O: filesystem (writeFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync)\n  - [x] 5.4: Target 100% coverage on new files\n\n- [x] Task 6: Integration verification (AC: all)\n  - [x] 6.1: `npm run build` — verify tsup compiles new files\n  - [x] 6.2: `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions (2842 tests, 110 files)\n  - [x] 6.3: Verify module boundaries: only barrel `index.ts` exports public API\n  - [x] 6.4: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9) — template: 109 lines, tests: 294 lines\n  - [x] 6.5: Verify generated Dockerfile passes `validateDockerfile()` end-to-end (AC #5)\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Architecture References\n\nThis story implements FR22 (Dockerfile template based on project type) and FR25 (dev workflow prompts Dockerfile update on new deps). It builds on Story 4.1's `validateDockerfile()` and the existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` files. Architecture Decision 5 (Rules as Markdown) establishes the pattern.\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n\n**Template generation, not copying:** `generateDockerfileTemplate()` does NOT simply copy `templates/Dockerfile.verify` into the project. It generates a new Dockerfile based on detected stack type with appropriate content. The existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` is codeharness's own verification Dockerfile — the new template is for the user's project.\n\n**Stack detection reuse:** Use `detectStack()` from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` which already returns `'nodejs' | 'python' | null`. No new detection logic needed.\n\n**Idempotency (AC #4):** If a Dockerfile already exists, `generateDockerfileTemplate()` returns `fail('Dockerfile already exists')`. The init orchestrator handles this gracefully — log a skip message, continue init. This preserves the project's existing Dockerfile.\n\n**Compliance by construction (AC #5):** The generated templates MUST pass all 6 rule categories from Story 4.1. This is a design constraint — if the template doesn't pass validation, the template is buggy. Test this explicitly.\n\n**Dev workflow patch (AC #6):** Update `patches/dev/enforcement.md` with a Dockerfile maintenance section. This is a patch file — the dev agent reads it during implementation. No code execution, just documentation that guides agent behavior.\n\n**Comments in generated Dockerfiles (AC #7):** Each section of the generated Dockerfile gets a comment explaining its purpose. This helps developers maintain the Dockerfile when codeharness isn't involved.\n\n### Node.js Template Structure\n\n```dockerfile\n# Base image — pinned version for reproducibility\nFROM node:22-slim\n\nARG TARBALL=package.tgz\n\n# System utilities for verification\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n    curl \\\n    jq \\\n  && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Install project from tarball (black-box: no source code)\nCOPY ${TARBALL} /tmp/${TARBALL}\nRUN npm install -g /tmp/${TARBALL} && rm /tmp/${TARBALL}\n\n# Run as non-root user\nUSER node\n\nWORKDIR /workspace\n```\n\n### Python Template Structure\n\n```dockerfile\n# Base image — pinned version for reproducibility\nFROM python:3.12-slim\n\n# System utilities for verification\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n    curl \\\n    jq \\\n  && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Install project from wheel or sdist\nCOPY dist/ /tmp/dist/\nRUN pip install /tmp/dist/*.whl && rm -rf /tmp/dist/ && pip cache purge\n\n# Run as non-root user\nUSER nobody\n\nWORKDIR /workspace\n```\n\n### Existing Code to Reuse\n\n- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` — `validateDockerfile()` to verify generated templates pass all rules\n- `src/modules/infra/index.ts` — barrel file to export new `generateDockerfileTemplate`\n- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — init orchestrator to integrate template generation\n- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — `InitResult` type to extend with `dockerfile` field\n- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — `detectStack()` for project type detection\n- `src/types/result.ts` — `Result<T>`, `ok()`, `fail()` for return types\n- `templates/Dockerfile.verify` — reference for Node.js template content (codeharness's own)\n- `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` — reference for generic template content\n- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — dev workflow patch to update with Dockerfile maintenance\n\n### What This Story Does NOT Include\n\n- No `docker build` execution — template generation is file I/O only\n- No Dockerfile linting beyond `validateDockerfile()` — Story 4.1 handles validation\n- No auto-updating of Dockerfiles when dependencies change — the dev workflow _prompts_ the agent, it doesn't auto-modify\n- No multi-stage build templates — keep it simple, single-stage for now\n- No CI/CD Dockerfile generation — this is for verification Dockerfiles only\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- **Depends on:** Story 4.1 (dockerfile-validator, `validateDockerfile()`) — DONE\n- **Depended on by:** None in current sprint\n\n### File Size Constraint\n\nEach new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9.\n- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — ~80-120 lines (template generation)\n- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — ~150-250 lines (tests)\n- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — modification only, adding ~10 lines\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 4.1 Dockerfile Validator)\n\n- **`validateDockerfile()` checks 6 rule categories.** Generated templates must pass all 6.\n- **`DockerfileGap` has `{ rule, description, suggestedFix, line? }`.** Use `validateDockerfile()` in tests to verify templates.\n- **`loadRules()` falls back to hardcoded defaults.** Templates don't need `patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md` to validate — defaults suffice.\n- **Barrel imports only.** Import from `../infra/index.js`, not from `dockerfile-template.js` directly.\n- **The `Result<T>` pattern** uses `ok()` and `fail()` from `src/types/result.ts`.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits show Story 4.1 complete. The project uses:\n- Commander for CLI commands\n- `Result<T>` discriminated union for error handling\n- tsup for building\n- Vitest for testing\n- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) for module boundaries\n- `detectStack()` returns `'nodejs' | 'python' | null`\n- Init orchestrator in `init-project.ts` composes sub-steps sequentially\n- `InitResult` type in `types.ts` structures the init output\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 5] — Rules as Markdown, validator approach\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 4.2] — Acceptance criteria\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR22] — Dockerfile template based on project type\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR25] — Dev workflow prompts Dockerfile update\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts] — Validator to verify generated templates\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts] — Init orchestrator to integrate template generation\n- [Source: templates/Dockerfile.verify] — Reference Node.js verification Dockerfile\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- New files: `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts`, `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`\n- Modified files: `src/modules/infra/index.ts` (add barrel export), `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` (integrate template generation), `src/modules/infra/types.ts` (extend InitResult), `patches/dev/enforcement.md` (add Dockerfile maintenance section)\n- Module follows existing conventions: barrel exports, Result<T> returns, <300 line files\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.proof.md`)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/infra/AGENTS.md)\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.md`\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] All I/O mocked (filesystem, subprocess, HTTP)\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Implementation Notes\n\n- Templates use single-line `apt-get install` format because `validateDockerfile()` checks each line independently for tool presence on install lines. Multi-line continuation (`\\`) splits across lines and the validator doesn't join them.\n- Generic template uses `npm install -g placeholder` as a binary install placeholder to satisfy the binary-on-path rule. Users must replace this.\n- Template generation is synchronous — only file I/O, no subprocess calls.\n- All 3 template variants (nodejs, python, generic) pass all 6 rule categories with zero gaps, verified by dedicated test cases.\n\n### Completion Notes\n\nAll 6 tasks complete. 22 new tests added in dockerfile-template.test.ts covering: template content for all 3 stacks, existing Dockerfile idempotency, Result<T> type contract, validateDockerfile() compliance, and inline comments. Full regression suite passes (2842 tests, 110 files). Build succeeds. No new dependencies added.\n\n## File List\n\n- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — new\n- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — new\n- `src/modules/infra/index.ts` — modified\n- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — modified\n- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — modified\n- `src/modules/infra/AGENTS.md` — modified\n- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — modified\n- `docs/exec-plans/active/4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration.md` — new\n\n## Change Log\n\n- 2026-03-21: Implemented Story 4.2 — Dockerfile template generation for nodejs/python/generic stacks, integrated into init flow, updated dev enforcement patch with Dockerfile maintenance guidance, 22 unit tests added.\n","numLines":252,"startLine":1,"totalLines":252}}}
